                            <comment id="134041" author="niu" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 03:09:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks the stuck chmod isn&apos;t necessarily from test_91.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Stopping client onyx-37vm6.onyx.hpdd.intel.com /mnt/lustre opts:
Stopping client onyx-37vm5.onyx.hpdd.intel.com /mnt/lustre opts:
COMMAND  PID USER   FD   TYPE      DEVICE SIZE/OFF               NODE NAME
chmod   4569 root  cwd    DIR 1273,181606   282624 144115188193296385 /mnt/lustre
/mnt/lustre is still busy, wait one second
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pid of the stuck chmod is 4569. (The pid number is pretty small)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;== sanityn test 91: chmod and unlink striped directory == 08:00:08 (1447344008)
start pid 31563 to chmod striped directory
start pid 31564 to unlink striped directory
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pid of chmod from test_91 is 31563.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But there isn&apos;t any further information (logs, stack trace, etc.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
